gomodel:SYNGO_2110  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4/5; Rich2 activity is needed for spine enlargement induced by chemical LTP and increase of synaptic currents, and increase of surface levels of synaptic AMPARs [fixed tissue] (NMDAR activation)[Rich2 KD, OE Rich2 mutant proteins]\n\nFig.7; Rich2 interaction with Shank3 is needed for cLTP induced exocytosis of GluR1, spine enlargement. Experimental description: \"Neuronal hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryos of either sex of E-17 Swiss mice and grown in Neurobasal medium supplemented with B27 and 10% fetal bovine serum (FBS).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-11" ;
